.TH COUNTDOWN 1 "2025-11-24" "version 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
countdown \- simple terminal countdown timer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B countdown
duration [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B countdown
command runs a timer for the specified duration.  
Durations can be specified in seconds (10s), minutes (5m), or hours (1h).  
You can combine the duration with optional flags to customize behavior.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -m=MSG, --message=MSG
Display a custom message when the countdown finishes.
.TP
.B --sound
Play a sound when the countdown ends.
.TP
.B --quiet
Suppress live countdown output; only final message is displayed.
.TP
.B --progress
Show a progress bar during the countdown.
.TP
.B --endtime
Show the expected end time of the countdown.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Display this help message.
.TP
.B -v, --version
Display the countdown version.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
countdown 10s
Run a 10-second timer.
.TP
countdown 1m --progress
Show a 1-minute countdown with progress bar.
.TP
countdown 30s -m="Break over!"
Display a custom message when done.
.TP
countdown 2m --quiet --sound
Silent countdown with audio alert.
